-- FTN Cocoa of Nigeria Retreats the Most in Two Weeks as Profit Declines 94%
-- B y   V i n c e n t   N w a n m a
-- 2010-12-22T12:43:37Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-22/ftn-cocoa-of-nigeria-retreats-the-most-in-two-weeks-as-profit-declines-94-.html
FTN Cocoa Processors Plc , a Nigerian
producer of commodities from the chocolate ingredient, fell the
most in two weeks after saying profit declined 94 percent in the
period through September.  Net income retreated to 12.4 million naira ($80,400) from
205.7 million naira a year earlier, according to a statement on
the website of the Lagos-based Nigerian Stock Exchange dated
yesterday. The bourse described the period as the third quarter.  FTN Cocoa had the biggest intraday drop since Dec. 8,
losing 3 kobo, or 4.6 percent, to 62 kobo by 1:21 p.m. in Lagos.
A close at level would be its lowest since Dec. 10.  Nigeria is the fourth-largest producer of the chocolate
ingredient, after the Ivory Coast, Ghana and Indonesia.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Vincent Nwanma  in Lagos at 
 vnwanma@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin in Johannesburg at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net . 